    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA191-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākac ceṟippaṟivuṟuppāṉ vēṇṭic (ET: tōḻi ceṟippaṟivuṟuppāḷ) colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said when HE was behind the fence, wishing to inform [him] about [HER] confinement.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA191">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ciṟuvī ñāḻaṟ ṟēṉṟō yoḷḷiṇar</l>
<l>            nēriḻai makaḷir vārmaṇa liḻaitta</l>
<l>            vaṇṭaṟ pāvai vaṉamulai muṟṟat</l>
<l>            toṇpoṟic cuṇaṅki ṉaitupaṭat tāaṅ</l>
<l>            kaṇṭal vēlik kāmar ciṟukuṭi </l>
<l>            yellivan taṉṟō tēreṉac colli</l>
<l>            yalareḻun taṉṟiv vūrē palaruḷu</l>
<l>            meṉṉōk kiṉarē yaṉṉai nāḷai</l>
<l>            maṇippū muṇṭakaṅ koyyē ṉāyi</l>
<l>            ṉaṉikkavi ṉuṇmaiyō varitē maṇikkaḻi </l>
<l>            naṟumpūṅ kāṉal vantavar</l>
<l>            vaṟuntēr pōta lataṉiṉu maritē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">        “Did a chariot come at night</l>
<l rend="indent">        to [our] desirable small hamlet with mangrove fences,</l>
<l rend="indent2">        where the honey-soaked bright clusters of the small-blossomed</l>
<l rend="indent2">         Ñāḻal are spreading, to be as pretty<note place="foot">T.V.G. takes <term xml:lang="ta">aitu-paṭa</term> as an adverb meaning either softly or slowly, but it seems possible to take it in a semantically more meaningful way.</note> as bright beauty spots,</l>
<l rend="indent3">        in the courtyard, on the beautiful breast of the play<note place="foot">T.V.G. explains here vaṇṭal not in his usual way as "play", but as "silt", that is, the material the doll is made of, because sand would not be sticky enough for the purpose. In any case, here it seems we have to imagine a human-shaped (and -sized) relief figure lying on the soil. Is this the explanation for the strange shifting between image and doll to be observed with the use of <term xml:lang="ta">pāvai</term>?</note> dolls</l>
<l rend="indent3">        made of wet(?) sand by women with fine jewels?”</l>
<l rend="indent4">            speaking thus</l>
<l>    gossip arose in this village.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            Among many,</l>
<l>    mother looked at me.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            Tomorrow,</l>
<l rend="indent3">        if I don't pluck the Muṇṭakam's sapphire flowers,</l>
<l>    the [further] being of [my] beauty, it [is] very difficult.</l>
<l>    More difficult than that [is] the going of his poor chariot,</l>
<l rend="indent3">        coming through the seashore grove with fragrant flowers</l>
<l rend="indent3">        by the sapphire[-coloured] backwaters.</l>
        </lg>
